Eyrit <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=buchalter>Buchalter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/03 5:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=64>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://mywebpages.comcast.net/wbbuch1/EQ/arrowhead.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: whoop de doo</span><hr size=1> Again we read yet another agruement stating that &quot;UN Inspectors can't find chemical/biological/nuclear weapons in Iraq, therefore Saddam doesn't have any&quot;...<br>
<br>
Let me try to break this down so you can understand it.<br>
<br>
A newborn infant has no concept of what is called &quot;object permenance&quot;.  Meaning, if I show a 2 month old baby a block, and then remove it from their sight, the infant does not understand that the block still exists.  Out of Sight, Out of Mind, so to speak.  This is why the game of peak-a-boo can be so entertaining to a baby.<br>
<br>
By the age of one year old, the infant begins to realize that the block continues to exist, despite the fact that it is no longer in view, and the infant will continue to look for the block knowing that it must be somewhere.<br>
<br>
So now let's apply this to our situation in Iraq...<br>
<br>
Saddam SHOWS the UN that he has a weapons arsenal.  He admits it.  He signs surrender documents stating that he has the weapons, and agrees to dismantle them and SHOW PROOF that they have been dismantled.<br>
<br>
Now a UN Inspections team shows up, and the weapons are not there.  Nor is there any evidence that the weapons have been dismantled.  The inspectors find only a fraction of the weapons which Saddam origianlly disclosed that he had.<br>
<br>
So out of sight out of mind, right?  The weapons magically disappeared, right?  They are not out in plain view, so they must not exist.<br>
<br>
Dig your head out of the sand, folks. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
